			<ns0:name>bradc...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110304265766688778552/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Apps that want to pretend they are using a file abstraction need to go through very messy 
JavaScript/NaCl linkage and glue code.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
It is extremely fragile, hard to setup, hard to maintain, etc.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Pepper will provide a more useful File IO interface, and it will be made available in NaCl.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
File IO is available and solves common use cases for games, shared libraries, etc.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
much faster startup time, Google can host more applications in our online gallery.
